        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:24:"News - AlternativeTo.net";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:3:"url";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"https://feed.alternativeto.net/favicon.png";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:34:"https://alternativeto.net/news/all";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}s:9:"copyright";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"AlternativeTo";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"item";a:15:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"Adobe Firefly&#039;s Quick Cut helps creators turn raw footage into a first video draft with AI";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/adobe-firefly-s-quick-cut-helps-creators-turn-raw-footage-into-a-first-video-draft-with-ai/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/adobe-firefly-s-quick-cut-helps-creators-turn-raw-footage-into-a-first-video-draft-with-ai/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Thu, 26 Feb 2026 13:00:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1603:"<p>Adobe is launching <strong>Quick Cut</strong> for its <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/adobe-firefly/about/">Firefly</a> video editor, aiming to help content creators assemble videos quickly from their own footage or generated clips. Quick Cut addresses a frequent pain point by enabling users to upload b-roll or generate new footage, and then instantly transform these materials into a structured first edit, eliminating the challenge of starting from an empty timeline.</p>
<p>Building on this automated start, Quick Cut offers a narrative-first assembly using a description supplied by the user. Additional customization options include providing a shot list or script for more precise edits, and making initial choices such as selecting aspect ratio, setting automatic pacing or a specific duration, and adding a B-roll track to keep supporting footage organized.</p>
<p>These new features are designed to give editors a clear starting point for shaping, refining, and personalizing their videos. By automating the initial cut, Quick Cut reduces the time spent manually stitching together clips, allowing creators to focus more on aspects like story, strategy, and narrative development.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/adobe-firefly-s-quick-cut-helps-creators-turn-raw-footage-into-a-first-video-draft-with-ai/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/adobe-firefly/about/">More about Adobe Firefly</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/adobe-firefly/">Adobe Firefly Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772056342258.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"Deno 2.7 brings stable Temporal API, Windows on ARM support &amp; better Node.js compatibility";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:130:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/deno-2-7-brings-stable-temporal-api-windows-on-arm-support-and-better-node-js-compatibility/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:130:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/deno-2-7-brings-stable-temporal-api-windows-on-arm-support-and-better-node-js-compatibility/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Thu, 26 Feb 2026 10:00:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2181:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/deno/about/">Deno</a> 2.7 is now available as the latest version of this open source runtime for <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/javascript/about/">JavaScript</a> and <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/typescript/about/">TypeScript</a>. This release introduces several headline features, beginning with the stabilization of the Temporal API. Developers no longer need the <code>--unstable-temporal</code> flag, allowing more consistent and reliable date and time operations across projects.</p>
<p>Alongside API enhancements, Deno now delivers official builds for Windows on ARM devices. This enables native performance on laptops such as the Surface Pro X and Snapdragon-powered ThinkPad X13s, removing the need for x86 emulation and meeting a longstanding user request.</p>
<p>Building on interoperability, Deno now offers first-class support for <code>package.json</code> files, including the overrides field. This helps developers manage dependency versions deep within their <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/node-js/about/">Node.js</a> project trees, reducing friction when migrating projects.</p>
<p>Following these developments, the update introduces new <code>Deno.spawn()</code>, <code>Deno.spawnAndWait()</code>, and <code>Deno.spawnAndWaitSync()</code> APIs, streamlining the process of running subprocesses compared to the previous <code>Deno.Command</code> API. The release also upgrades the <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/v8/about/">V8 JavaScript engine</a> to version 14.5, which brings performance improvements, bug fixes, and the latest JavaScript language features. Additional updates cover Node.js compatibility enhancements, general API and package manager changes, and various quality of life improvements.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/deno-2-7-brings-stable-temporal-api-windows-on-arm-support-and-better-node-js-compatibility/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/deno/about/">More about Deno</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/deno/">Deno Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772055161662.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"Atlassian introduces AI agents in Jira for enhanced automation and workflow integration";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/atlassian-introduces-ai-agents-in-jira-for-enhanced-automation-and-workflow-integration/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/atlassian-introduces-ai-agents-in-jira-for-enhanced-automation-and-workflow-integration/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Thu, 26 Feb 2026 08:30:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1860:"<p>Atlassian has introduced AI agents in <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/jira/about/">Jira</a>, bringing a new level of automation now available in open beta. Teams can assign work directly to agents or mention them in comments to prompt iteration or get specific follow-up actions. Agents display as assignees with standard Jira fields, making it easy for teams to recognize tasks handled by agents while tracking each item’s status within sprints, releases, or incidents.</p>
<p>Following this introduction, administrators are given fine-grained control to determine which agents are accessible to which users, in what contexts they can be used, and the specific criteria for marking tasks as complete. Individual exchanges with agents, including requests, agent responses, and final team decisions, are preserved in the relevant work item for complete transparency.</p>
<p>Agents can be embedded into Jira workflows, allowing them to perform certain jobs automatically within existing processes. In addition, agents adhere to Jira’s established project settings, permissions, and auditing features, ensuring that organizational standards are maintained. Because Atlassian’s <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/model-context-protocol/about/">Model Context Protocol (MCP)</a> creates an open and standardized interface, users can connect custom models and agents to Jira, integrate with proprietary tools and data, and configure agent actions directly within their workflows.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/atlassian-introduces-ai-agents-in-jira-for-enhanced-automation-and-workflow-integration/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/jira/about/">More about JIRA</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/jira/">JIRA Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772054459334.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"YouTube beefs up its $7.99 Premium Lite subscription with background play and downloads";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:125:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/youtube-beefs-up-its-7-99-premium-lite-subscription-with-background-play-and-downloads/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:125:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/youtube-beefs-up-its-7-99-premium-lite-subscription-with-background-play-and-downloads/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 19:00:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1730:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/youtube/about/">YouTube</a> is expanding its Premium Lite subscription by adding background play and video downloads. This update gives Lite users access to offline viewing and the ability to keep videos playing while using other apps, features previously limited to the standard Premium tier.</p>
<p>Starting today, these upgrades will become available and will reach all Premium Lite markets over the next few weeks. The enhancements are being made in response to subscriber feedback <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2025/3/youtube-expands-premium-lite-plan-to-the-us-offering-ad-free-viewing-for-7-99-per-month/">after YouTube widened the Premium Lite pilot to additional regions last year</a>.</p>
<p>With these new features, Premium Lite subscribers now get most videos ad-free, in addition to offline playback and background operation. However, while Premium Lite is closer to the full $12.99 per month Premium plan, some capabilities remain exclusive. Only full Premium removes all ad types, provides ad-free music videos, and enables features such as interface queueing.</p>
<p>Following these improvements, YouTube clarifies that Premium Lite, priced at $7.99 per month, will still show ads in some contexts, such as during search and browsing, even though the majority of video content is ad-free.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/youtube-beefs-up-its-7-99-premium-lite-subscription-with-background-play-and-downloads/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/youtube/about/">More about YouTube</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/youtube/">YouTube Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772033981222.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"Canva acquires Cavalry and Mango AI to expand 2D animation &amp; AI-powered intelligence tools";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:131:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/canva-acquires-cavalry-and-mango-ai-to-expand-2d-animation-and-ai-powered-intelligence-tools/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:131:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/canva-acquires-cavalry-and-mango-ai-to-expand-2d-animation-and-ai-powered-intelligence-tools/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 17:30:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1977:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/canva/about/">Canva</a> has announced the acquisition of <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/cavalry/about/">Cavalry</a>, a 2D animation software available for Mac and Windows, as well as <a href="https://mangoai.co">Mango AI</a>, a platform that showcases over 3,000 artificial intelligence websites across various domains. Cavalry will sit alongside <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/affinity-1/about/">Affinity</a> in Canva’s suite, creating a professional stack that covers static design, vector illustration, layout, and now, motion graphics.</p>
<p>Following these acquisitions, creatives can craft assets in Affinity and Cavalry’s precise design environments, then move effortlessly into Canva to collaborate, adapt, and distribute content across teams, formats, and channels. Canva users are assured that all free features within Cavalry will remain available at no cost. The Cavalry team will continue guiding the application’s future, retaining the founders’ vision but with increased resources from Canva.</p>
<p>By acquiring Mango AI, Canva gains additional expertise in data intelligence and reinforcement learning. Mango AI’s technology was developed to generate, launch, and automatically optimize video ads based on real-world performance, easing the creative process for marketing teams. Building on this, combining Mango AI with MagicBrief strengthens Canva’s intelligence layer, forming a feedback loop that ties together creation, actionable insight, and campaign results for creative and marketing professionals.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/canva-acquires-cavalry-and-mango-ai-to-expand-2d-animation-and-ai-powered-intelligence-tools/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/canva/about/">More about Canva</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/canva/">Canva Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772028896371.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"Wine 11.3 released with Mono 11, VKD3D 1.19, enhanced FIR filter in DirectSound, and more";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:125:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/wine-11-3-released-with-mono-11-vkd3d-1-19-enhanced-fir-filter-in-directsound-and-more/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:125:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/wine-11-3-released-with-mono-11-vkd3d-1-19-enhanced-fir-filter-in-directsound-and-more/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 16:00:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1697:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/wine/about/">Wine</a> 11.3 has been released, bringing expanded compatibility for running Windows applications on Linux, macOS, and BSD platforms. This update introduces a series of core enhancements aimed at improving both performance and compatibility for a wide range of users.</p>
<p>Among the main changes, Wine 11.3 updates the mono engine to version 11.0.0, benefitting applications dependent on Microsoft's .NET technology. The bundled VKD3D library has also been upgraded to version 1.19, improving support for Direct3D 12 and strengthening Wine's capabilities in running modern games and graphics-intensive programs. Additionally, users will notice an improved finite impulse response (FIR) filter in DirectSound, translating to enhanced audio handling for supported software.</p>
<p>Following these updates, Wine 11.3 introduces more optimizations for program database (PDB) loading, which can help in debugging and reduce startup overhead for some applications. The light theme has been renamed to Aero, improving compatibility with software that checks for traditional Windows theming.</p>
<p>Wine 11.3 also delivers 30 bug fixes covering a diverse set of applications, including Rainmeter, QuarkXPress 2024, Framemaker 8, and games such as Guild Wars 2 and Flight Simulator 2000.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/wine-11-3-released-with-mono-11-vkd3d-1-19-enhanced-fir-filter-in-directsound-and-more/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/wine/about/">More about Wine</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/wine/">Wine Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772024816593.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:77:"Discord is now delaying its global age verification plans after huge backlash";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:116:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-is-now-delaying-its-global-age-verification-plans-after-huge-backlash/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:116:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-is-now-delaying-its-global-age-verification-plans-after-huge-backlash/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:19:31 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2586:"<p>If you're not already tired of listening about the <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/about/">Discord</a> drama, you're in luck, because the platform <a href="https://discord.com/blog/getting-global-age-assurance-right-what-we-got-wrong-and-whats-changing">has now officially announced</a> that it is <strong>delaying its global age verification plan</strong>. Discord now says the rollout will not happen until the second half of 2026, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-will-require-global-age-verification-through-a-face-scan-or-id-for-full-access/">after huge backlash</a> over privacy concerns and confusion, admitting it did a poor job explaining the policy and left many users thinking face scans and ID uploads would be required just to use Discord. It is worth noting though that <strong>Discord is not backing out</strong>, and it still intends to roll out the change globally once the updated approach is ready.</p>
<p>Until then, age verification <strong>will remain limited to places where it is legally required</strong>, including the UK and Australia, with Brazil expected to join soon. In those regions, adults who want to access age restricted content will still need to verify through third party providers such as k-ID.</p>
<p>Discord says facial age estimation partners will need to run fully on device, with no biometric processing in the cloud, and it points to <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-ends-persona-partnership-after-backlash-over-age-verification-and-palantir-ties/">moving away from Persona</a>, a Peter Thiel backed company tied to Palantir interest, after a UK test raised concerns about surveillance and security. It also says it stopped working with a previous vendor tied to a breach involving scanned IDs. Next, Discord plans to add more verification methods, including credit card checks, though it says local laws in the UK, Australia, and Brazil may limit what options are available. It also plans to add spoiler channels as an alternative to age gated channels, and to publish vendor documentation, technical details on age estimation, and ongoing transparency metrics about verification prompts and methods.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-is-now-delaying-its-global-age-verification-plans-after-huge-backlash/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/about/">More about Discord</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/">Discord Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772023288341.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"1Password to raise subscription prices for individual and family plans by up to 33%";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:122:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/1password-to-raise-subscription-prices-for-individual-and-family-plans-by-up-to-33-/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:122:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/1password-to-raise-subscription-prices-for-individual-and-family-plans-by-up-to-33-/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 11:55:14 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1295:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/1password/about/">1Password</a> will increase subscription prices starting March 27th, 2026, according to an email sent to users.</p>
<p>The individual plan will rise from $3.99 to $4.99 per month and from $35.88 to $47.88 per year, while the family plan will rise from $6.95 to $7.99 per month and from $59.88 to $71.88 per year. In both tiers, the annual price change is $12, and the new rates apply at the next renewal if it occurs after March 27th, 2026, meaning the subscription <strong>will increase by as much as 33%.</strong></p>
<p>1Password said its pricing has stayed largely unchanged for many years while the product expanded in features and security, and that the increase will support continued investment in innovation and security. The company pointed to recent additions like saving logins and payment details, phishing protection, and faster device setup.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/1password-to-raise-subscription-prices-for-individual-and-family-plans-by-up-to-33-/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/1password/about/">More about 1Password</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/1password/">1Password Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1772021362390.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:94:"Tuta introduces schedule send feature to Tuta Mail &amp; event invite updates to Tuta Calendar";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:131:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/tuta-introduces-schedule-send-feature-to-tuta-mail-and-event-invite-updates-to-tuta-calendar/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:131:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/tuta-introduces-schedule-send-feature-to-tuta-mail-and-event-invite-updates-to-tuta-calendar/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 08:30:00 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1738:"<p>Tuta has introduced a schedule send feature to its mail service, allowing users to choose exactly when their emails are delivered. With this update, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/tutanota/about/">Tuta Mail</a> users can reply and schedule emails to be sent at times that suit their preferences, enhancing user control over communication timing.</p>
<p>Following these mail improvements, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/tuta-calendar/about/">Tuta Calendar</a> now makes it easier to manage event invitations. When a user receives an invitation but has not yet accepted or declined, the event appears on the calendar with a faint appearance and a dotted outline, labeled as a ghost bubble. This visual distinction helps users differentiate between pending and confirmed calendar events.</p>
<p>These feature updates follow just six days after <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/tuta-mail-and-calendar-now-offer-official-open-source-thunderbird-add-ons-for-easier-use/">Tuta released official Thunderbird add-ons for both Tuta Mail and Tuta Calendar</a>, highlighting a period of rapid development. Looking ahead, Tuta has announced ongoing work on an undo send function and improvements to spam filtering. The upcoming changes aim to further reduce unwanted email and ensure legitimate messages reach users’ inboxes.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/tuta-introduces-schedule-send-feature-to-tuta-mail-and-event-invite-updates-to-tuta-calendar/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/tutanota/about/">More about Tuta Mail</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/tutanota/">Tuta Mail Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771954730536.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"Notion 3.3 launches custom agents for autonomous team automation";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:103:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/notion-3-3-launches-custom-agents-for-autonomous-team-automation/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:103:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/notion-3-3-launches-custom-agents-for-autonomous-team-automation/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 05:26:29 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1913:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/notion/about/">Notion 3.3</a> has been launched, introducing &quot;<a href="https://www.notion.com/releases/2026-02-24">Custom Agents</a>&quot;, its flagship new AI feature aimed at enabling autonomous automation for teams. Once configured, agents run without manual prompting, using triggers or schedules to keep work moving. Teams can co-create and share agents, with permission controls managed similarly to teammate access.</p>
<p>Custom Agents connect with <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/slack/about/">Slack</a>, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/figma/about/">Figma</a>, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/linear/about/">Linear</a>, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/hubspot/about/">HubSpot</a>, Notion content, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/notion-mail/about/">Notion Mail</a>, and <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/notion-calendar/about/">Notion Calendar</a> via MCP. Agents are set up with plain language instructions, and users can define triggers, sources, and the AI model for each agent.</p>
<p>Notion includes templates for Q&amp;A, task routing, and status update workflows, such as answering repeat questions, routing requests to owners, and generating standups or sprint recaps from connected context. The company says early testers created over 21,000 agents and that it runs 2,800 internally, with admin controls for access and audit logs. Custom Agents are free through May 3, 2026, then will require Notion credits starting May 4, 2026.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/notion-3-3-launches-custom-agents-for-autonomous-team-automation/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/notion/about/">More about Notion</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/notion/">Notion Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771998139722.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"Firefox 148 has been released and finally introduces an AI controls panel for its AI tools";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/firefox-148-has-been-released-and-finally-introduces-an-ai-controls-panel-for-its-ai-tools/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/firefox-148-has-been-released-and-finally-introduces-an-ai-controls-panel-for-its-ai-tools/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Wed, 25 Feb 2026 05:08:26 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2431:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/firefox/about/">Firefox 148</a> is adding a new <strong>AI Controls</strong> panel in Settings that lets desktop users manage Firefox generative AI features from one place. It covers tools like generative AI page translations, PDF image alt text suggestions, AI enhanced tab group naming and related tab suggestions, link preview key points, and the sidebar AI chatbot with providers including <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/chatgpt/about/">ChatGPT</a>, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/google-bard/about/">Gemini</a>, and <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/google-bard/about/">Copilot</a>. The rollout also follows <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2025/12/after-backlash-over-firefox-ai-plans-a-dev-clarifies-users-can-fully-disable-ai-features/">earlier backlash over Firefox adding more AI powered tools</a>, and Mozilla <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/mozilla-details-new-user-controls-for-blocking-ai-features-that-are-coming-in-firefox-148/">had indicated</a> controls like this would be part of how users could manage what is enabled.</p>
<p>The panel includes both per feature dropdowns and a single Block AI enhancements toggle that hides current and future generative AI features, including promotions. Each feature can be set to Available, Enabled, or Blocked, and blocking removes any on device models tied to that feature. Blocking also affects extensions that use AI provided by Firefox, but it does not stop extensions from using third party AI services independently.</p>
<p>Firefox 148 also includes improved screen reader support for mathematical formulas in PDFs, remote improvements that can be enabled without opting into telemetry or studies, expanded translation support including Traditional Chinese and Vietnamese, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/windows-10/about/">Windows 10</a> backup support for users who clear history on close with exclusions for cleared data, plus bug fixes and security updates.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/firefox-148-has-been-released-and-finally-introduces-an-ai-controls-panel-for-its-ai-tools/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/firefox/about/">More about Mozilla Firefox</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/firefox/">Mozilla Firefox Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771996904646.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:11;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:68:"Clonezilla Live 3.3.1-35 adds 4kn/512 disk cloning and tool upgrades";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:107:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/clonezilla-live-3-3-1-35-adds-4kn-512-disk-cloning-and-tool-upgrades/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:107:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/clonezilla-live-3-3-1-35-adds-4kn-512-disk-cloning-and-tool-upgrades/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Tue, 24 Feb 2026 16:04:16 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:971:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/clonezilla/about/">Clonezilla Live</a> 3.3.1-35 enables cloning between 4kn and 512n/e disks and includes a new tool for converting partition tables. The release upgrades its base to <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/debian/about/">Debian</a> Sid with <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/linux-kernel/about/">Linux kernel</a> 6.18.9-1 and brings enhanced <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/windows-bitlocker/about/">BitLocker</a> support.
Major bugs affecting network cloning, device detection, and disk restoration are also resolved.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/clonezilla-live-3-3-1-35-adds-4kn-512-disk-cloning-and-tool-upgrades/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/clonezilla/about/">More about Clonezilla</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/clonezilla/">Clonezilla Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771949056366.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:12;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"Apple Sports launches in Latin America and the Caribbean";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/apple-sports-launches-in-latin-america-and-the-caribbean/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/apple-sports-launches-in-latin-america-and-the-caribbean/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Tue, 24 Feb 2026 15:49:50 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:605:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/apple-sports/about/">Apple Sports</a> is now available in Latin America and the Caribbean. Users in these regions can check real-time scores and stats from their preferred leagues using their iPhone.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/apple-sports-launches-in-latin-america-and-the-caribbean/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/apple-sports/about/">More about Apple Sports</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/apple-sports/">Apple Sports Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771948190775.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:13;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"Discord ends Persona partnership after backlash over age verification and Palantir ties";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-ends-persona-partnership-after-backlash-over-age-verification-and-palantir-ties/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:126:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-ends-persona-partnership-after-backlash-over-age-verification-and-palantir-ties/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Tue, 24 Feb 2026 09:25:11 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3381:"<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/about/">Discord</a> has confirmed it has now ended its relationship with <a href="https://withpersona.com">Persona</a>, an age verification and identity assurance provider, after sustained backlash over face scans and ID uploads tied to <a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-will-require-global-age-verification-through-a-face-scan-or-id-for-full-access/">its upcoming global age verification push</a>. Discord head of product policy Savannah Badalich said the company's experiment with Persona has now concluded. Persona has also drawn scrutiny because it is used by <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/reddit/about/">Reddit</a> and <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/roblox/about/">Roblox</a>, and because it has received backing <strong>from Peter Thiel’s Founders Fund, tied to Palantir</strong>, which has sharpened surveillance concerns for many users.</p>
<p>Those concerns escalated further after <a href="https://www.therage.co/persona-age-verification/">researchers reported</a> finding exposed code and thousands of files linked to Persona on <strong>a US government authorized endpoint</strong>, pointing to extensive verification checks, watchlist style screening, and risk scoring. The materials were described as accessible without an exploit, and reporting also suggested parts of the system appeared to be powered by an OpenAI powered chatbot. <a href="https://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2026/02/discord-and-persona-end-partnership-after-shady-uk-age-test-sparks-outcry/?utm_campaign=dhtwitter&amp;utm_content=%3Cmedia_url%3E&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=twitter">Persona’s CEO said</a> Discord related verification data was deleted immediately and denied having US government contracts, while confirming communication with researchers after the exposure.</p>
<p>Discord later clarified that its Persona work had been a limited UK test, where age assurance had already launched. The company is now naming <a href="https://www.k-id.com">k ID</a>, with support for ID verification via Veratad, as its listed vendors, and has repeatedly stressed that its facial age estimation happens <strong>locally on your device, with the video selfie staying on device rather than being uploaded.</strong> Discord says identity document images and ID match selfies <strong>are deleted once an age group is confirmed</strong>, and that most users will not be prompted unless it cannot determine adulthood with high confidence, as it keeps reevaluating vendors while the rollout expands under heavier privacy and surveillance scrutiny.</p>
<p>Btw, if this still doesn't do enough to rebuild trust, <a href="https://x.com/AlternativeTo/status/2023427437439381890">we recently shared a short list</a> of open-source <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/">Discord alternatives</a> on our social channels, so feel free to check it out and share your personal recommendation too 😉</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/discord-ends-persona-partnership-after-backlash-over-age-verification-and-palantir-ties/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/about/">More about Discord</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/discord-app/">Discord Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771928885698.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:14;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:87:"
            
            
            
            
            
            
        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:90:"Anthropic accused DeepSeek and other Chinese AI labs of using Claude to train their models";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/anthropic-accused-deepseek-and-other-chinese-ai-labs-of-using-claude-to-train-their-models/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/anthropic-accused-deepseek-and-other-chinese-ai-labs-of-using-claude-to-train-their-models/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Tue, 24 Feb 2026 08:53:03 GMT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2220:"<p>Anthropic is accusing three Chinese AI labs, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/deepseek/about/">DeepSeek</a>, <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/minimax-ai-1/about/">MiniMax</a>, and <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/kimi-ai/about/">Moonshot AI (Kimi)</a>, of misusing its <a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/claude/about/">Claude model</a> to improve their own AI products. The company claims the activity involved about <strong>24,000 fraudulent accounts and more than 16 million interactions with Claude</strong>, which it describes as industrial scale campaigns. Anthropic says the goal was <strong>distillation</strong>, where a smaller model learns from a more capable model’s outputs, and argues that doing this without permission can give competitors a shortcut to advanced capabilities without comparable investment.</p>
<p>Anthropic warns that models produced through illicit distillation may not carry over key safety safeguards, increasing the risk of misuse. It says these systems could be applied to military, intelligence, or mass surveillance use cases, including offensive cyber operations or disinformation campaigns. Anthropic claims DeepSeek ran at least <strong>150,000 targeted exchanges</strong> focused on Claude’s reasoning abilities and on generating censorship safe alternatives to sensitive topics, while MiniMax and Moonshot logged <strong>over 13 million and 3.4 million exchanges.</strong></p>
<p>Anthropic is urging AI companies, cloud providers, and policymakers to address distillation, and suggests tighter limits on access to advanced chips to reduce the scale of these efforts. The claims land amid an ongoing US debate over chip export policies to China, and broader concerns about national security and economic risks tied to &quot;unauthorized model extraction&quot;.</p>
<p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/news/2026/2/anthropic-accused-deepseek-and-other-chinese-ai-labs-of-using-claude-to-train-their-models/">View article on AlternativeTo &raquo;</a></p><p><a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/claude/about/">More about Claude</a>&nbsp;|&nbsp;<a href="https://alternativeto.net/software/claude/">Claude Alternatives</a></p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"enclosure";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"url";s:65:"https://img.alternativeto.net/news/1520x760/jpg/1771924123805.png";s:6:"length";s:1:"0";s:4:"type";s:9:"image/png";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:"type";i:128;s:7:"headers";a:11:{s:3:"age";s:1:"8";s:13:"cache-control";s:34:"public, max-age=0, must-revalidate";s:16:"content-encoding";s:2:"br";s:12:"content-type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"date";s:29:"Thu, 26 Feb 2026 13:45:38 GMT";s:6:"server";s:6:"Vercel";s:25:"strict-transport-security";s:16:"max-age=63072000";s:4:"vary";s:59:"RSC, Next-Router-State-Tree, Next-Router-Prefetch, Next-Url";s:14:"x-matched-path";s:9:"/news/all";s:14:"x-vercel-cache";s:3:"HIT";s:11:"x-vercel-id";s:44:"bom1::iad1::6z9qz-1772113547245-ab2c10d95321";}s:5:"build";i:1769365239;s:13:"cache_version";i:1;s:4:"hash";s:40:"0a933902882a430f430ab7e438d95256667f9b8a";s:21:"cache_expiration_time";i:1772113607;s:23:"__cache_expiration_time";i:1772114347;}